Original:
The Sparrow's Debt

A barrister and a detective, once childhood friends, are set on a collision course when a murder case unearths a dark secret they thought was buried forever.

Series Overview

Set against the backdrop of late 1980s London, this thriller follows two lives torn apart by a shared past. Alicia Hemsworth is a fiercely idealistic barrister determined to prove the innocence of her client, a man accused of murdering a prominent socialite. On the other side is Detective Inspector Patrick Davies, the meticulous investigator convinced he has the right man.

Their professional rivalry is complicated by a deep, unresolved bond forged in a children's home years ago. As the case unfolds, coded messages and threats from their past begin to surface, all linked to a mysterious figure they both fear. Alicia and Patrick must navigate a web of lies, power, and memory, where the killer they're hunting might be closer to their own history than they could ever imagine.

Characters

Alicia "Ali" Hemsworth (29)

A sharp, passionate, and rising star at the bar. Her unwavering belief in justice stems from a childhood where she felt powerless. She is haunted by fragmented memories of her time at the children's home and her bond with Patrick.

Patrick "Paddy" Davies (29)

A brilliant and respected Detective Inspector known for his rigid adherence to protocol. He uses the structure of the law to control a world he learned early on was chaotic and dangerous. He is fiercely protective of Alicia, even if it means keeping her at arm's length.

Episode Breakdown

Episode 1: The First Stone

HOOK: A close-up on a bloody designer scarf on a marble floor. The camera tilts up to reveal Alicia’s client, JULIAN CROFT, looking terrified as police lights flash across his face.





Alicia sits opposite Julian in a sterile interview room. His hands tremble.



JULIAN: "I didn't do it. I found her like that, I swear."



In a packed briefing room, Patrick points to a evidence board, his expression cold.



PATRICK: "All evidence points to one man. Julian Croft."



In a crowded courthouse corridor, Alicia and Patrick lock eyes for the first time in years. A flash of recognition, then a wall of professionalism.



Patrick walks past, stopping to hold up a plastic evidence bag. Inside is a small, crudely carved wooden sparrow.

CLIFFHANGER: Alicia sees the sparrow and her face drains of all color. She stumbles back against the wall, a forgotten memory hitting her like a physical blow.

Episode 2: The Old Signal

HOOK: A grainy, faded photograph in Alicia’s hand. A young, smiling Alicia and Patrick, his arm around her. She is clutching an identical wooden sparrow.





In her office late at night, Alicia confronts Julian with a sketch of the bird.



ALICIA: "Have you ever seen this before?"



JULIAN: "No, never! What is it?"



Patrick stares at a crime scene photo on his desk, a nagging doubt in his mind. He answers a ringing desk phone.



ALICIA (V.O.): "That bird. It means something."



PATRICK: "It's evidence in a murder case, Alicia. Stay out of it."



ALICIA (V.O.): "It's a message, Paddy. And you know it."

CLIFFHANGER: Patrick slams the phone down. He goes to his flat and pulls a dusty, wooden box from under his bed. He opens it, revealing an identical, weathered wooden sparrow nestled inside.

Episode 3: The Warning

HOOK: A shadowy figure in a trench coat watches Alicia from a rain-slicked alley as she leaves her chambers late at night.





Patrick finds a note slipped under his office door. Scrawled handwriting reads: "WRONG MAN. ASK ABOUT THE SPARROWS."



Alicia discovers her client, Julian, was having an affair with the victim. She storms into the prison visitation room.



ALICIA: "You lied to me! Why?"



JULIAN: "I was scared! She knew things... she was going to ruin me!"



Patrick reviews the victim's phone records. He sees a series of calls from a blocked number in the week before her death.

CLIFFHANGER: Alicia returns to her dark flat. She pushes the door and it swings open—it's already unlocked. She freezes on the threshold, her heart pounding.

Episode 4: The Sparrow's Mark

HOOK: Alicia walks slowly through her ransacked apartment. Nothing is stolen. It’s been searched. On her bathroom mirror, scrawled in red lipstick, is a single word: SPARROW.





Alicia meets Patrick in a clandestine spot under a bridge, showing him a photo of the mirror.



PATRICK: "This has gone too far. Drop the case, Ali. Now."



ALICIA: "Not until I know why they're using our past to frame my client."



PATRICK: "You think this is about your client? This is a warning. To us."



He grips her arm, his professional mask slipping for a second, revealing genuine fear.

CLIFFHANGER: Patrick, breaking protocol, drives to the derelict, gated entrance of the old St. Jude's Children's Home. He shines his torch on the muddy ground and finds a set of fresh, adult-sized footprints leading inside.

Episode 5: The Name in the Book

HOOK: A jarring, quick-cut flashback: A child’s hand (Young Patrick) presses a wooden sparrow into a crying Young Alicia’s hand. His voice whispers, "I'll always protect you."





Alicia, at her desk, finds a link: the murder victim was a major anonymous donor to St. Jude's for years.



Patrick walks through the decaying halls of the children's home. In the old warden's office, he finds a dust-covered admissions ledger.



He blows the dust off the cover and flips it open. He runs his finger down a list of names.



His finger stops. A single name has been recently, viciously circled in red ink: "Michael Thorne." Patrick recoils, a name he clearly fears.

CLIFFHANGER: Alicia's office phone rings. She answers. A distorted, electronic voice speaks. "You and the detective should have left the sparrows to sleep. Now Michael knows you're awake." The line goes dead.

